  <p>The free application <a href="http://koala-app.com/">Koala</a> was used to compile the SASS files in this theme </p>
  <h3 class="demo-title">Using Koala to compile SASS files</h3>
  <p>The first time you run <a href="http://koala-app.com/">Koala</a> a screen similar to the one below should open.</p>
  <img src="images/help/koala-1.jpg" alt="image" class="margin-b"/>
  <p>The next thing you should do is load the included <strong>Sass</strong> files. You do this by locating the entire <i>sass</i> directory in windows explorer and dragging it to the app as indicated. Once you do this Koala will try to list all the <strong>Sass</strong> files it can find in the directory. </p>

  <img src="images/help/koala-2.jpg" alt="image" class="margin-b"/>
  <p>Only select <code>uikit.scss</code> since it references all the other SASS files. Make sure to de-select the <strong>compass mode</strong> option on the right then click <strong>compile.</strong> Thats it ! <code>uikit.scss</code> should be compiled to <code>uikit.css</code> and <strong>copied to the css folder</strong>.</p>

  <h3 class="demo-title">compiling changes</h3>
  <p>Whenever you edit any of the the stylesheets, always run <a href="http://koala-app.com/">Koala</a> and compile the changes.</p>
  
  <!-- Callout -->
  <div class="bs-callout bs-callout-info">
    <h4>Sass rules are similar to CSS!</h4>
    <p>Sass files should be treated just like regular css files. Use the same properties, values and syntax that you would use with a css stylesheet.</p>
  </div>
  <!-- /Callout -->
  
  <h3 class="demo-title">Auto compiling changes</h3>
  <p>If you do not want to click compile everytime you make changes, simply select the auto-compile option on the right. Now <a href="http://koala-app.com/">Koala</a> will watch all the files in the <strong>sass</strong> directory and automatically compile any changes.</p>

  <!-- Callout -->
  <div class="bs-callout bs-callout-info">
    <h4>Remember to compile any new changes!</h4>
    <p>The main stylesheets <code>uikit.scss</code> needs to be compiled every time you make changes. You can <b>select the Auto Compile option</b> in Koala to <b>automate</b> this process.</p>
  </div>
  <!-- /Callout -->

  <h3 class="demo-title">Compressing Stylesheets</h3>
  <p>If you want compress the generated files, simply select the desired compression level found in the options. Koala will remember the setting even if you have selected a file to be auto compiled.</p>

